Quick-moving Hurricane Delta has made landfall in Louisiana as a Category 2 storm, near the town of Creole with maximum sustained winds of 100 mph.

Delta breaks the record for most named storms to make landfall in one season in the continental U.S. https://t.co/pJfl7lajiR https://t.co/NnABfKrvdZ

RT @ABCNewsLive: The @WFP won the #NobelPeacePrize for its efforts to combat hunger in regions facing conflict and hardship at a time when the COVID-19 pandemic has driven people to the brink of starvation.
